<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Inradius">Inradius</h2></di=
v>
<p>The inradius (the radius of a circle <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org=
/wiki/Inscribed" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Inscribed">inscribed</a> in=
 the rhombus), denoted by <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>r</i></span>, can be e=
xpressed in terms of the diagonals <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>p</i></span> =
and <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>q</i></span> as<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Mathworld=
_11-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rhombus=
#cite_note-Mathworld-11"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>10<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
